<h3 class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-zeniaRosaOscuro pt-2">CAVITATION AND RADIOFREQUENCY</h3>
<p><strong class="font-bold underline text-zeniaRosaOscuro">Cavitation</strong> and <strong class="font-bold underline text-zeniaRosaOscuro">radiofrequency</strong> are an ideal combination: the former treats localised fat and the latter acts as a firming agent once the fat is eliminated.</p>
<p><strong class="font-bold text-zeniaMarronOscuro">What is cavitation?</strong><br/><strong class="font-bold underline text-zeniaRosaOscuro">Cavitation</strong> is a non-surgical procedure that applies <strong class="font-bold underline text-zeniaRosaOscuro">low-frequency ultrasound</strong> to the target area, causing fat cells to dissolve and be eliminated naturally.</p>
